results.name: a(n) = round( n / pi(n)) = round( A000027(n) / A000720(n) ).
comment: This sequence grows very slowly. First n for which a(n) = 5 is 190, then 556 for 6, 1821 for 7, etc. - Alonso del Arte, Feb 27 2012
example: a(7) = 2 because pi(7) = 4 and 7/4 = 1.75, which rounds up to 2.
results.author: _Jonathan Vos Post_ and _Robert G. Wilson v_, May 17 2005
